In honor of Religious Freedom Day, President Donald Trump issued a proclamation reaffirming the commitment to safeguarding the religious liberty of all Americans. He highlighted the historical significance of religious freedom in America, from the Pilgrims seeking a new land to the Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom authored by Thomas Jefferson. The First Amendment further solidified the protection of religious freedom. President Trump emphasized his administration's commitment to protecting religious liberty, citing executive orders and actions taken to advance religious freedom and combat anti-Semitism. The administration also prioritizes protecting religious minorities abroad, condemning repressive governments and terrorist organizations that persecute individuals based on their beliefs. The proclamation calls on all Americans to commemorate Religious Freedom Day and work towards securing this blessing both domestically and globally.